%% ------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Complexity Analysis}
\label{sec:complexity}
%% ------------------------------------------------------------

\subsection{Formal Decision Problem}

\begin{quote}
\emph{Given a board $B$, parameters $m$ and $k$, a symbol assignment, and a wall set $W$, does a valid solution to the 3DSRP instance exist?}
\end{quote}

\subsection{Membership in NP}

The 3DSRP is in \textbf{NP}. Given a proposed partition into $m$ regions, a verifier checks validity through the following steps, each running in polynomial time and verifiable by the human eye on the physical puzzle:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Coverage check:} Verify that every cube belongs to exactly one region. Takes $\mathcal{O}(c)$ time and is visually immediate on the physical object by checking if every exterior face holds a colored marker associated with a region.

    \item \textbf{Connectivity check:} For each region, perform a breadth-first search without crossing walls to verify all its cubes are reachable from one another. Takes $\mathcal{O}(c)$ time total and can be physically verified by tracing connected cubes of the same color.

    \item \textbf{Non-planarity check:} For each region, verify that its cubes do not all share the same $x,y,z$ coordinate. A region is planar if all its cubes have the same value on one axis, this is immediately visible on the physical puzzle since a flat region cannot stand up in three directions. Takes $\mathcal{O}(c)$ time.

    \item \textbf{Symbol completeness check:} Count the occurrences of each symbol type in each region. Takes $\mathcal{O}(c)$ time. Due to the board's full visibility property, all symbols are located on outer faces, making this check immediate by visual inspection.

    \item \textbf{Wall separation check:} For each wall, verify the two adjacent cubes belong to different regions. Takes $\mathcal{O}(|W|)$ time. Walls are physically visible as barriers between cubes of different colors.
\end{enumerate}

The entire verification runs in $\mathcal{O}(c + |W|)$, confirming that 3DSRP is in NP.

